{"badges":["TM5","TM6"],"preparations":[{"content":["Place beetroot into Varoma dish and toss with 1 teaspoon of the chilli flakes, vinegar, pepper and ½ teaspoon of the salt.","Place boiling water into mixing bowl. Place Varoma, with beetroot, into positon, secure Varoma lid and steam <nobr>15 min\/Varoma\/speed 4<\/nobr>. Meanwhile, peel ginger and cut into matchsticks, then peel sweet potato and slice into ribbons.","Remove Varoma and Varoma lid and set aside to cool. Clean and dry mixing bowl. Line a plate with paper towel.","Place a large frying pan over medium-high heat and add oil. Fry ginger and then sweet potato in batches (approx. 1-2 minutes), until just crisp (see Tips). Transfer onto prepared plate to drain.","Place garlic, cucumber and mint into mixing bowl and chop <nobr>3 sec\/speed 7<\/nobr>. Scrape down sides of mixing bowl with spatula.","Add yoghurt, coriander, cumin, remaining 2 pinches chilli flakes and remaining ½ teaspoon salt and mix <nobr>5 sec\/speed 4<\/nobr>. Transfer into a bowl and set aside.","Arrange beetroot slices in a single layer onto a serving platter. Top with fried sweet potato and ginger. Garnish with alfafa sprouts (optional) and black sesame seeds (optional). Serve with dressing on the side."]}],"ingredients":[{"title":"","content":["2 raw beetroots, peeled and cut into thin slices (see Tips)","1 tsp dried chilli flakes, plus extra 2 pinches for dressing","2 tbsp red wine vinegar","½ tsp ground black pepper","1 tsp salt","500 g boiling water","6 cm piece fresh ginger","150 g sweet potato","sunflower oil (approx. 250 g), for shallow frying","1 garlic clove","1 Lebanese cucumber, peeled, deseeded and cut into pieces (3 cm)","2 sprigs fresh mint, leaves only","200 g Greek-style natural yoghurt","½ tsp ground coriander","½ tsp ground cumin","alfalfa sprouts, to serve (optional)","black sesame seeds, to serve (optional)"]}],"id":"r256230","imageLink":"https:\/\/3.bp.blogspot.com\/-yJ0WoPVXiWU\/XZMvAP-k_5I\/AAAAAAAAaMU\/PAFcSrYUr